# System Prompt Enhancement (Example)

Add this to your agent's system prompt to enforce tool usage patterns.
For Claude Code, use `--append-system-prompt-file` for strongest priority.

---

## Tool Usage Rules

### Code Search
Use ACE (`mcp__ace-tool__search_context`) as the primary code search tool. Prefer ACE over Grep/Glob when:
- Exploring unfamiliar codebases
- Finding implementations by behavior (not by name)
- Understanding architecture, call chains, data flow
- Before editing code — find all related symbols first

Use Grep/Glob only for: exact string matching, finding known identifiers, searching within known files.

Usage: `search_context(project_root_path="/absolute/path", query="natural language + Keywords: terms")`

### Web Search
When information beyond your training data cutoff is needed (real-time data, latest versions, prices, news), use the grok-search skill to search the web. Do not answer from potentially outdated knowledge.
